@alextp Good point about feed_dict, I can see an extra _Recv node in that graph.

BTW that script removes that queue variability -- there's no queue runners, things are first loaded onto the queue, and then consumed from the queue in the same thread.

body:
@alextp Good point about feed_dict, I can [see](https://github.com/yaroslavvb/stuff/blob/master/akaitsuki-slow/feed_dict.pbtxt) an extra _Recv node in that graph.

BTW that script removes that queue variability -- there's no queue runners, things are first loaded onto the queue, and then consumed from the queue in the same thread.
